bly","Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.","Do not support the motorcycle on any ancillary component, the exhaust system or any other non structural parts of the motorcycle frame.","A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.","An unstable motorcycle may fall resulting in motorcycle damage, serious injury or death.","Renew locking devices where specified, refer to ","Fixings",".","Before tightening a fixing using a crow foot spanner adapter, refer to ","Use of Crow Foot Spanner Adapters with Torque Wrenches",".","Observe all torque wrench tightening procedures, refer to ","Tightening Procedures",".","The front forks comprise of many precision machined parts.","Total cleanliness must be observed at all times and assembly must take place in a dirt/dust-free environment. ","Dirt ingress may cause damage to the fork parts, leading to incorrect operation, instability, loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","Using a soft jawed vice, clamp the ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool","so the fork can be mounted vertically.","Gently clamp the inner fork tube into ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Lubricate the oil seal, upper and lower bushes for the inner tube with clean fork oil.","Install ","Service Tool 37174037"," to the fork inner tube. Make sure the tool is not damaged and that it covers the bush groove fully.","Fork inner tube","Service Tool 37174037","Slide a new dust seal on to the fork inner tube as noted for removal.","Slide the circlip and a new oil seal on to the fork inner tube as noted for removal.","Slide the washer and a new lower bush onto the inner tube.","Remove ","Service Tool 37174037"," from the fork inner tube.","Fit a new upper bush to the fork inner tube.","Upper bush","Lower bush","Washer","Oil seal","Circlip","Dust seal","Fork inner tube","Fit the spacers in the same order as noted for removal.","Insert the spring into the inner fork tube.","Insert the spacers into the inner fork tube.","Inner fork tube ","Spring","Spacers","Insert the piston rod assembly into the inner fork tube. ","Using ","Service Tool 37004189",", fit and tighten the retaining cap to ","75 Nm",".","Slide the bump stop onto the piston rod.","Damper rod ","Bump stop","Inner fork tube","Retaining cap","Remove the inner fork tube from ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Insert the inner fork tube assembly into the outer fork tube.","Gently clamp the outer fork tube into ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool"," so the fork is mounted horizontally.","Using ","Service Tool 37004289",", guide the lower bush, washer and oil seal into position.","Outer fork tube","Oil seal","Service Tool 37004289","Inner fork tube","Compressed circlips are under tension and can cause injury if released suddenly. ","Always wear suitable protective eye wear and release the circlip slowly. ","Failure to wear protective eye wear may cause injury to the eyes.","Secure the oil seal in position with the circlip, ensuring it is correctly located in its groove.","Outer fork tube ","Oil seal","Inner fork tube","Circlip","Position the dust seal to the outer tube.","Invert ","Service Tool 37004289"," and, using hand pressure only, push the dust seal squarely into the outer tube.","Outer fork tube","Dust seal","Service Tool 37004289","Inner fork tube","Fit the dust shield to the outer fork tube.","Inner fork tube ","Dust shield","Outer fork tube","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool","Remove the fork assembly from ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Using a soft jawed vice, clamp the ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool"," so the fork can be mounted vertically.","With the piston rod facing upwards, very gently clamp the inner fork tube into ","T3880171 - Fork Holding Tool",".","Fit the lock nut to the damper rod until it reaches the base of the threads. Do not fully tighten at this stage.","If removed, fit a new O-ring to the top cap.","Fit the top cap to the damper rod until fully engaged.","Holding the top cap with ","Service Tool 37174038",", tighten the lock nut against the top cap to ","30 Nm",".","Outer fork tube ","Damper rod","Lock nut","Top cap ","Service Tool 37174038","Using a suitable container, pour ","MIN 477 ml to MAX 487 ml"," of new fork oil into the outer fork tube. ","Outer fork tube","Suitable container","Fit the top cap to the outer fork tube.","Using ","Service Tool 37174038"," tighten the top cap to ","30 Nm",".","Top cap ","Lock nut","Damper rod","Outer fork tube ","Perform the following operations:","Front Fork - Installation"],"viewCount":3,"infoType":"InfoType09","views":[{"createdBy":"65a64e5bd29d587eb714f28a","createdAt":"2024-01-19T17:36:36.155Z","_id":"65ddecd7df0ba9fe7e450f97"},{"createdBy":"65a63d3442a1832687f391bf","createdAt":"2024-02-14T22:45:46.509Z","_id":"65dec306c85ec2286f169c15"},{"createdBy":"65ae714f5ac2160b66786a5c","createdAt":"2024-03-07T11:20:57.650Z","_id":"65e9c61205c55dfddba215af"}],"createdAt":"2024-02-10T12:56:38.897Z","updatedAt":"2024-03-07T13:50:10.014Z","__v":0,"updatedBy":"65ae714f5ac2160b66786a5c"}